{"article_id":"PcEnyfXUuvajSKyt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The U.S. lost 701,000 jobs in March ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"breaking a remarkable string of uninterrupted payrolls gains the past decade","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"and revealing just the leading edge of the coronavirus-triggered hurricane","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"that 's upending America ' s economy and labor market .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The unemployment rate jumped from a 50-year low of 3.5 % to 4.4 % , highest since August 2017 ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"the Labor Department said Friday .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"That 's also the sharpest monthly rise in unemployment since January 1975 ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"according to TD Economics .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The report reflects employers ' jitters early in the month over the unprecedented economic fallout from the pandemic .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"But it doesn ' t capture the nearly 10 million laid-off and furloughed Americans","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"who filed initial jobless claims the past two weeks","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"as much of the nation ' s economy was shut down","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"to contain the spread of the virus .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"That ' s because Labor ' s survey was conducted the week","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"ending March 14 ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"before most states ordered residents to stay at home","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and nonessential businesses","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"-- such as restaurants , movie theaters and most stores --","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"to close .","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"`` This is terrible","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"but unfortunately it 's nothing","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"compared to what 's coming in April , ''","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"says Ian Shepherdson , chief economist of Pantheon Macroeconomics .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"Still , the 701,000 payroll losses are the most","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"since 800,000 jobs were shed in March 2009 during the depths of the Great Recession","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"and they end a record 113-month streak of gains","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"dating to October 2010 .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Economists","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"surveyed by Bloomberg","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"estimated","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"that 100,000 jobs were lost last month .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"U.S. stocks turned lower Friday in another volatile trading session","depth":5},{"id":32,"text":"after the government reported the big job losses .","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"Also pushing the market lower :","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"energy stocks gave up gains","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"as crude prices lost momentum .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"The Dow Jones industrial average slumped about 500 points","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"and the Standard & Poor ' s 500 fell 2.2 % in early afternoon trading .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Friday 's report does capture the first stumble in the economy ' s historic free fall .","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"The number of workers","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"filing initial jobless claims","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"rose by 70,000","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"- the most since 2013 --","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"to 282,000 the week of Labor ' s survey .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Yet Morgan Stanley reckoned","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"the March employment figure mostly would underscore a sharp pullback in hiring by nervous businesses rather than the more recent wave of staggering layoffs .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Net job gains or losses in any month are a combination of new hiring and job cuts .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"Goldman Sachs , however , believes","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"the March tally could signify substantial layoffs as well ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"noting","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"that some of the 3.3 million Americans","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"filing first-time jobless claims the week","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"ending March 21","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"likely were let go the previous week .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"The number unemployed people rose by 1.4 million last month ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Friday 's report shows .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"On Thursday , Labor said","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"another 6.6 million workers filed claims last week .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"All told ,","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"Oxford Economics estimates","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"the outbreak will result in 24 million job losses and a 14 % unemployment rate in April alone , above the 10 % peak","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"reached during the Great Recession of 2007-09 .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Further job cuts should push unemployment to a peak of 16 % in May ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"says Oxford Chief U.S . Economist Gregory Daco .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"By comparison , it took about two years for the economy to lose nearly nine million jobs during the Great Recession .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Shamike Brown , 34 , of Conway , South Carolina , lost her dream job as a specialist","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"dealing with children ' s developmental delays","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"just three weeks after landing the position .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Parents had stopped letting such specialists into their homes .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"since she was a new hire ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"she was the first","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"let go .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"`` Everybody was so proud of me","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"and now I have nothing","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"to show , ''","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"Brown says .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"The single mother of two applied for unemployment benefits","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"but got a message","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that she was ineligible","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"because of a technical mistake","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"she made","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"while applying .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Her numerous calls to the state employment office have gone unanswered .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"`` I 'm worried about how I 'm going to pay my bills and get food , \"","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"Brown says .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"\" I have kids at home","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"that I have to homeschool","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"and I 'm trying not to let them see me stressed or worried about anything . ''","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Most analysts say","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"the economy is is already mired in a deep","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"-- but likely short --","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"recession .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Capital Economics predicts","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"gross domestic output will fall at a stunning 40 % annual rate in the second quarter .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"Assuming","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"the outbreak begins to wane by summer ,","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"economists expect a strong rebound in the second half of the year","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"as shuttered businesses reopen .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"In the meantime , the $ 2.2 trillion dollar stimulus","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"passed by Congress","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"is intended to encourage many small businesses to retain , or rehire , employees","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"by promising to forgive loan to firms","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"that maintain staffs .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Still , the massive layoffs and lingering consumer fears of contagion could leave the economy diminished for some time , with unemployment","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"that falls","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"but remains elevated","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"compared to pre-crisis levels .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"In a sign of the economy 's breathtaking turnabout , U.S. employers added well over 200,000 jobs in both January and February .","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"Labor on Friday revised down gains for the two months by a total 59,000 .","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"But that still leaves strong payroll increases of 214,000 for January and 275,000 for February .","depth":6},{"id":111,"text":"Historic layoffs :","depth":4},{"id":112,"text":"A record 6.6M Americans file for unemployment benefits","depth":5},{"id":113,"text":"as coronavirus wreaks havoc on economy","depth":5},{"id":114,"text":"States in the crosshairs :","depth":4},{"id":115,"text":"Which states will be hit hardest by coronavirus-related job losses ?","depth":5},{"id":116,"text":"See the list .","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"As expected ,","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"leisure and hospitality was hit hardest , with 459,000 job losses ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"though even that total reflects just the initial surge of cuts","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"walloping the industry .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"Healthcare lost 61,000 jobs ;","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"professional and business services , 52,000 ; retail , 46,000 ; construction , 29,000 ; and manufacturing , 18,000 .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"The numbers show the breadth of the pandemic 's impact across the economy .","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"Even auto and other manufacturers have closed factories","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"because of fears of infection .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"And professional businesses such as law and marketing firms are cutting jobs","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"even though their white-collar employees can work from home","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"as much of the economy remains paralyzed by uncertainty .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"Government was among the few insulated sectors ,","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"adding 12,000 jobs ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"including 18,000 by the federal government , mostly temporary employees for the 2020 census .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"The 4.4 % unemployment rate highlights only part of the economic devastation","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"wrought by the outbreak .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"A broader measure of unemployment","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"-- that includes Americans","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"working part-time","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"even though they want full-time jobs ,","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"discouraged workers","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"who have stopped looking","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"and the unemployed -","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"leaped from 7 % , near a 20-year low , to 8.7 % , highest since March 2017 .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"The share of Americans","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"working or looking for jobs","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"tumbled from a seven-year high of 63.4 % to 62.7 % , lowest since late 2017 .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"That further reveals","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"that the official unemployment rate doesn ' t capture all of the workers","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"pushed to the sidelines by the economic blows of the pandemic .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"Average hourly earnings increased 11 cents to $ 28.62 ,","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"bumping up the annual gain from 3.1 % to 3 % .","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"Many of the workers","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"losing jobs last month","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"were low-paid restaurant and retail workers ,","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"and that could have nudged average pay increases higher ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"economists said","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"Wage growth has hovered around 3 % the past year","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"despite falling unemployment","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"that made it tougher for businesses to find qualified workers .","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"Now , the recession is leaving a surplus of workers","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"that 's likely to push pay increases lower .","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"`` Wage growth will likely slow sharply over the next few months , ''","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"Shepherdson says .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":323,"left":250,"right":322,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":200,"right":249,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":192,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":192,"left":180,"right":191,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":165,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":0,"right":164,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":1,"right":163,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":163,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":169,"right":178,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":168,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":166,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":167,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":172,"right":177,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":170,"right":171,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":173,"right":176,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":173,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":15,"right":175,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":174,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":183,"right":190,"relation":"adversative","nu